{"title_page": "Starship Entertainment", "text_new": "{{Short description|South Korean record label}}\n{{infobox company\n| name             = Starship Entertainment<ref>[https://www.bloomberg.com/Research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapid=253118840 Bloomberg Businessweek]</ref>\n| native_name      = \uc2a4\ud0c0\uc27d \uc5d4\ud130\ud14c\uc778\uba3c\ud2b8\n| native_name_lang = ko\n| logo             = Starship Entertainment.png\n| type             = [[Public]] company \n| traded_as        = \n| founder          = Kim Shi-dae\n| key_people       = Kim Shi-dae (CEO)\n| industry         = {{unbulleted list|[[Entertainment]]|}}\n| genre            = {{unbulleted list|[[K-pop]]|[[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]|[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]|[[Electronic Music|Electronic]]|[[Contemporary folk music|Contemporary folk]]}}\n| services         = {{unbulleted list|Music production | Publishing| Artists management}}\n| revenue          = \n| parent           = [[Kakao M]]<br />(since 2013)\n| owner            =  [[Kakao M]] (70%)\n| num_employees    = \n| divisions        = [[King Kong Entertainment|King Kong by Starship]] (since 2015)\n| subsid           = Starship X (2013)<br />House of Music (2017)\n| footnotes        = \n| profit           = \n| slogan           = \n| homepage         = {{URL|http://www.starship-ent.com/}}\n| caption          = \n| foundation       = {{Start date|2008|01|28}}\n| former_name      = \n| location_city    = [[Myeongdong]],  [[Seoul]]\n| location_country = [[South Korea]]\n| locations        = \u2022 Bongeunsa-ro<br />\u2022  [[Samseong-dong]]<br />\u2022 [[Gangnam District|Gangnam-gu]] \n}}\n\n'''Starship Entertainment''' ({{ko-hhrm|\uc2a4\ud0c0\uc27d \uc5d4\ud130\ud14c\uc778\uba3c\ud2b8}}) is a South Korean entertainment company established in 2008 by founder Kim Shi Dae.\n\nThe label is home to [[K-Pop]] artists such as [[K.Will]], [[Soyou]], OG School Project, [[Jooyoung]], [[Monsta X]], Cravity, Wonho, [[Yoo Seung-woo]], [[Brother Su]], [[Cosmic Girls]], [[Gun (rapper)|#Gun]], [[Mind U]], [[Duetto (duo)|Duetto]], [[Jeong Se-woon]],<ref>[http://search.nate.com/search/all.html?q=%BD%BA%C5%B8%BD%B1+%BF%A3%C5%CD%C5%D7%C0%CE%B8%D5%C6%AE&csn=0&asn=001200370&ml=1&tq=&rq=&nq=2&sg=&fss=&tid=&hlid=&clid=&cbid= \"\uc2a4\ud0c0\uc27d \uc5d4\ud130\ud14c\uc778\uba3c\ud2b8\"], ''Naver''. Retrieved 22 October 2011. {{in lang|ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|script-title=ko:\ubcf4\uc774\ud504\ub80c\ub4dc, \uc6d0\uc22d\uc774 \uc721\ud3ec \ub4dc\uc154\ubcf4\uc168\ub098\uc694?|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20111104n19067|publisher=Nate|accessdate=4 November 2011|language=Korean}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\ubcf4\uc774\ud504\ub80c\ub4dc, \uc77c\ubcf8 NHK \ubc29\uc1a1\ucd9c\uc5f0 '\uc2e0\uc778\ubd88\uad6c \uc774\ub840\uc801 \ud3b8\uc131'|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20111018n04927|publisher=Nate|accessdate=4 November 2011|language=Korean}}</ref> and formerly to [[Sistar]], [[Boyfriend (band)|Boyfriend]], [[Junggigo]], and [[Mad Clown]]. It also manages the actors Choi Won-myeong, [[Dasom]] and Kang Eun-ah. It operates in three main locations and is staffed with approximately 200 employees, funded by both commercial investors and its parent company, [[Kakao M]].\n\n== History ==\nThe company's founder, Kim Shi-dae, previously worked as a road manager for a K-pop band named [[cool (South Korean band)|Cool]] and worked for [[Bang Si-hyuk]]'s company [[Big Hit Entertainment]] between 2005 and 2007 before establishing his own company. Starship's first artist was [[K.Will]], followed by [[Sistar]], [[Boyfriend (band)|Boyfriend]], [[Monsta X]], [[Cosmic Girls]], and [[Jeong Se-woon]].\n\nOn 18 December 2013, 70% of the label's shares was acquired by its distributor, [[Kakao M]] (formerly LOEN Entertainment), making it an independent subsidiary of the latter.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2013/12/loen-entertainment-takes-over-majority-stake-in-starship-entertainment-for-15-billion-won|title=Loen Entertainment takes over majority stake in Starship Entertainment for 15 billion won|author=alim17|date=December 18, 2013|work=[[allkpop]]|accessdate=December 19, 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2015, Starship Entertainment had acquired 100% of King Kong Entertainment's shares in a strategic partnership alliance. On 2 January 2017, Starship Entertainment and King Kong Entertainment registered their merger. The agencies mutually agreed to use the name Starship Entertainment while the division that manages the actors will be operating under the label \u201cKing Kong by Starship\u201d.\n\n== Partnerships ==\n* {{Flagicon|JPN}} [[Being Inc.|Being Group]]<ref name=\"being\">{{cite web |title=We Are Boyfriend to be Released on June 6, 2012! |url=http://boyfriend-jp.com/news/120417.html |publisher=[[Being Inc.|Being Group]] |date= |access-date=May 3, 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120507045135/http://boyfriend-jp.com/news/120417.html |archive-date=May 7, 2012 |df= }}</ref>\n* {{Flagicon|JPN}} Kiss Entertainment\n* {{Flagicon|CHN}} [[Yuehua Entertainment]]\n* {{Flagicon|JPN}} [[Universal Music Japan]]\n\n== Artists ==\nAll artists under Starship Entertainment are collectively known as '''Starship Planet'''.\n\n=== Musicians ===\n{{Div col|colwidth=25em}}\n\n====Soloists====\n* [[K.Will]]\n* [[Soyou]]\n* [[Jeong Se-woon|Jeong Sewoon]]\n\n====Groups====\n* [[Monsta X]]\n* [[Cosmic Girls]] (WJSN) (with [[Yuehua Entertainment]])\n* Cravity\n\n====Duos/project groups====\n* [[Mind U]]\n* [[Duetto (duo)|Duetto]]\n* YTeen (with [[KT Corporation|KT]])\n*OG School Project (with [[Cube Entertainment]])\n*YDPP (with [[Brand New Music]])\n*[[WJMK (band)|WJMK]] (with [[Fantagio|Fantagio Music]])\n\n====Starship X====\n* [[Jooyoung]]\n* [[Brother Su]]\n* [[Gun (rapper)|#Gun]]\n* [[Kiggen]]\n\n====Starship Y====\n* [[Yoo Seung-woo]]\n\n====Highline====\n* Wonho is daddy material\n* DJ Soda\n* PLUMA\n* dress\n* DJ Vanto\n* Chang Sukhoon\n* Leon\n* ROVXE\n* M1NU\n* Lil Reta\n* DJ H.One\n\n====Notable Trainees====\n* Jang Won-young - [[Iz*One]]\n* [[Ahn Yu-jin]] - [[Iz*One]]\n\n{{div col end}}\n\n=== Actors/actresses ===\n{{further|King Kong by Starship}}\n\n== Former artists ==\n{{Div col|colwidth=}}\n*[[Sistar]] (2010\u20132017)\n**[[Yoon Bora]] (2010\u20132017)\n**[[Hyolyn]] (2010\u20132017)\n*[[Boyfriend (band)|Boyfriend]] (2011\u20132019)\n\n===Starship X===\n* [[Junggigo]] (2013\u20132018)\n* [[Mad Clown]] (2013\u20132018)\n\n===House of Music===\n* MoonMoon (2017\u20132018; contract terminated due to occlusion of a formal criminal record)<ref>https://www.soompi.com/2018/05/24/singer-moonmoon-revealed-probation-hidden-camera-crime-agency-ends-contract/</ref>\n{{div col end}}\n\n== Discography ==\n{{Main|Starship Entertainment discography}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{official website|http://www.starship-ent.com/}} {{in lang|ko}}\n\n{{Starship Entertainment}}\n{{LOEN Entertainment |state=collapsed}}\n{{K-pop}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Starship Entertainment}}\n[[Category:2008 establishments in South Korea]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Seoul]]\n[[Category:Companies established in 2008]]\n[[Category:Hip hop record labels]]\n[[Category:Labels distributed by Kakao M]]\n[[Category:Music publishing companies]]\n[[Category:Pop record labels]]\n[[Category:Publishing companies established in 2008]]\n[[Category:Rhythm and blues record labels]]\n[[Category:Starship Entertainment| ]]\n[[Category:Soul music record labels]]\n[[Category:South Korean record labels]]\n[[Category:Talent agencies of South Korea]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|South Korean record label}}\n{{infobox company\n| name             = Starship Entertainment<ref>[https://www.bloomberg.com/Research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapid=253118840 Bloomberg Businessweek]</ref>\n| native_name      = \uc2a4\ud0c0\uc27d \uc5d4\ud130\ud14c\uc778\uba3c\ud2b8\n| native_name_lang = ko\n| logo             = Starship Entertainment.png\n| type             = [[Public]] company \n| traded_as        = \n| founder          = Kim Shi-dae\n| key_people       = Kim Shi-dae (CEO)\n| industry         = {{unbulleted list|[[Entertainment]]|}}\n| genre            = {{unbulleted list|[[K-pop]]|[[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]|[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]|[[Electronic Music|Electronic]]|[[Contemporary folk music|Contemporary folk]]}}\n| services         = {{unbulleted list|Music production | Publishing| Artists management}}\n| revenue          = \n| parent           = [[Kakao M]]<br />(since 2013)\n| owner            =  [[Kakao M]] (70%)\n| num_employees    = \n| divisions        = [[King Kong Entertainment|King Kong by Starship]] (since 2015)\n| subsid           = Starship X (2013)<br />House of Music (2017)\n| footnotes        = \n| profit           = \n| slogan           = \n| homepage         = {{URL|http://www.starship-ent.com/}}\n| caption          = \n| foundation       = {{Start date|2008|01|28}}\n| former_name      = \n| location_city    = [[Myeongdong]],  [[Seoul]]\n| location_country = [[South Korea]]\n| locations        = \u2022 Bongeunsa-ro<br />\u2022  [[Samseong-dong]]<br />\u2022 [[Gangnam District|Gangnam-gu]] \n}}\n\n'''Starship Entertainment''' ({{ko-hhrm|\uc2a4\ud0c0\uc27d \uc5d4\ud130\ud14c\uc778\uba3c\ud2b8}}) is a South Korean entertainment company established in 2008 by founder Kim Shi Dae.\n\nThe label is home to [[K-Pop]] artists such as [[K.Will]], [[Soyou]], OG School Project, [[Jooyoung]], [[Monsta X]], Cravity, Wonho, [[Yoo Seung-woo]], [[Brother Su]], [[Cosmic Girls]], [[Gun (rapper)|#Gun]], [[Mind U]], [[Duetto (duo)|Duetto]], [[Jeong Se-woon]],<ref>[http://search.nate.com/search/all.html?q=%BD%BA%C5%B8%BD%B1+%BF%A3%C5%CD%C5%D7%C0%CE%B8%D5%C6%AE&csn=0&asn=001200370&ml=1&tq=&rq=&nq=2&sg=&fss=&tid=&hlid=&clid=&cbid= \"\uc2a4\ud0c0\uc27d \uc5d4\ud130\ud14c\uc778\uba3c\ud2b8\"], ''Naver''. Retrieved 22 October 2011. {{in lang|ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|script-title=ko:\ubcf4\uc774\ud504\ub80c\ub4dc, \uc6d0\uc22d\uc774 \uc721\ud3ec \ub4dc\uc154\ubcf4\uc168\ub098\uc694?|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20111104n19067|publisher=Nate|accessdate=4 November 2011|language=Korean}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\ubcf4\uc774\ud504\ub80c\ub4dc, \uc77c\ubcf8 NHK \ubc29\uc1a1\ucd9c\uc5f0 '\uc2e0\uc778\ubd88\uad6c \uc774\ub840\uc801 \ud3b8\uc131'|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20111018n04927|publisher=Nate|accessdate=4 November 2011|language=Korean}}</ref> and formerly to [[Sistar]], [[Boyfriend (band)|Boyfriend]], [[Junggigo]], and [[Mad Clown]]. It also manages the actors Choi Won-myeong, [[Dasom]] and Kang Eun-ah. It operates in three main locations and is staffed with approximately 200 employees, funded by both commercial investors and its parent company, [[Kakao M]].\n\n== History ==\nThe company's founder, Kim Shi-dae, previously worked as a road manager for a K-pop band named [[cool (South Korean band)|Cool]] and worked for [[Bang Si-hyuk]]'s company [[Big Hit Entertainment]] between 2005 and 2007 before establishing his own company. Starship's first artist was [[K.Will]], followed by [[Sistar]], [[Boyfriend (band)|Boyfriend]], [[Monsta X]], [[Cosmic Girls]], and [[Jeong Se-woon]].\n\nOn 18 December 2013, 70% of the label's shares was acquired by its distributor, [[Kakao M]] (formerly LOEN Entertainment), making it an independent subsidiary of the latter.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2013/12/loen-entertainment-takes-over-majority-stake-in-starship-entertainment-for-15-billion-won|title=Loen Entertainment takes over majority stake in Starship Entertainment for 15 billion won|author=alim17|date=December 18, 2013|work=[[allkpop]]|accessdate=December 19, 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2015, Starship Entertainment had acquired 100% of King Kong Entertainment's shares in a strategic partnership alliance. On 2 January 2017, Starship Entertainment and King Kong Entertainment registered their merger. The agencies mutually agreed to use the name Starship Entertainment while the division that manages the actors will be operating under the label \u201cKing Kong by Starship\u201d.\n\n== Partnerships ==\n* {{Flagicon|JPN}} [[Being Inc.|Being Group]]<ref name=\"being\">{{cite web |title=We Are Boyfriend to be Released on June 6, 2012! |url=http://boyfriend-jp.com/news/120417.html |publisher=[[Being Inc.|Being Group]] |date= |access-date=May 3, 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120507045135/http://boyfriend-jp.com/news/120417.html |archive-date=May 7, 2012 |df= }}</ref>\n* {{Flagicon|JPN}} Kiss Entertainment\n* {{Flagicon|CHN}} [[Yuehua Entertainment]]\n* {{Flagicon|JPN}} [[Universal Music Japan]]\n\n== Artists ==\nAll artists under Starship Entertainment are collectively known as '''Starship Planet'''.\n\n=== Musicians ===\n{{Div col|colwidth=25em}}\n\n====Soloists====\n* [[K.Will]]\n* [[Soyou]]\n* [[Jeong Se-woon|Jeong Sewoon]]\n\n====Groups====\n* [[Monsta X]]\n* [[Cosmic Girls]] (WJSN) (with [[Yuehua Entertainment]])\n* Cravity\n\n====Duos/project groups====\n* [[Mind U]]\n* [[Duetto (duo)|Duetto]]\n* YTeen (with [[KT Corporation|KT]])\n*OG School Project (with [[Cube Entertainment]])\n*YDPP (with [[Brand New Music]])\n*[[WJMK (band)|WJMK]] (with [[Fantagio|Fantagio Music]])\n\n====Starship X====\n* [[Jooyoung]]\n* [[Brother Su]]\n* [[Gun (rapper)|#Gun]]\n* [[Kiggen]]\n\n====Starship Y====\n* [[Yoo Seung-woo]]\n\n====Highline====\n* Wonho\n* DJ Soda\n* PLUMA\n* dress\n* DJ Vanto\n* Chang Sukhoon\n* Leon\n* ROVXE\n* M1NU\n* Lil Reta\n* DJ H.One\n\n====Notable Trainees====\n* Jang Won-young - [[Iz*One]]\n* [[Ahn Yu-jin]] - [[Iz*One]]\n\n{{div col end}}\n\n=== Actors/actresses ===\n{{further|King Kong by Starship}}\n\n== Former artists ==\n{{Div col|colwidth=}}\n*[[Sistar]] (2010\u20132017)\n**[[Yoon Bora]] (2010\u20132017)\n**[[Hyolyn]] (2010\u20132017)\n*[[Boyfriend (band)|Boyfriend]] (2011\u20132019)\n\n===Starship X===\n* [[Junggigo]] (2013\u20132018)\n* [[Mad Clown]] (2013\u20132018)\n\n===House of Music===\n* MoonMoon (2017\u20132018; contract terminated due to occlusion of a formal criminal record)<ref>https://www.soompi.com/2018/05/24/singer-moonmoon-revealed-probation-hidden-camera-crime-agency-ends-contract/</ref>\n{{div col end}}\n\n== Discography ==\n{{Main|Starship Entertainment discography}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{official website|http://www.starship-ent.com/}} {{in lang|ko}}\n\n{{Starship Entertainment}}\n{{LOEN Entertainment |state=collapsed}}\n{{K-pop}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Starship Entertainment}}\n[[Category:2008 establishments in South Korea]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Seoul]]\n[[Category:Companies established in 2008]]\n[[Category:Hip hop record labels]]\n[[Category:Labels distributed by Kakao M]]\n[[Category:Music publishing companies]]\n[[Category:Pop record labels]]\n[[Category:Publishing companies established in 2008]]\n[[Category:Rhythm and blues record labels]]\n[[Category:Starship Entertainment| ]]\n[[Category:Soul music record labels]]\n[[Category:South Korean record labels]]\n[[Category:Talent agencies of South Korea]]\n", "name_user": "77.28.133.191", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eHighline)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Starship_Entertainment"}
{"title_page": "Garnet (Steven Universe)", "text_new": "{{pp-protected|reason=Persistent addition of [[WP:INTREF|unsourced or poorly sourced content]]|small=yes}}\n{{Redirect|Garnet (character)|other characters with the same name|Garnet (disambiguation)#Characters}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE: Garnet (''Steven Universe'')}}\n{{Infobox character\n| color              = maroon\n| name               = Garnet\n| series             = [[Steven Universe]]\n| image              = File:Garnet - Steven Universe.png\n| caption            = Garnet as she appears in \"[[Change Your Mind (Steven Universe)|Change Your Mind]]\"\n| first              = Garnet ([[Television pilot|Pilot]]; 2013)<br/>Ruby and Sapphire ([[Jail Break (Steven Universe)|Jail Break]]; 2015)\n| last               = Ruby and Sapphire (I am My Monster; 2020)<br>Garnet ([[The Future]]; 2020)\n| creator            = [[Rebecca Sugar]]\n| voice              = [[Estelle (musician)|Estelle]]\n| lbl1               = Voice of Ruby\n| data1              = [[Charlyne Yi]]\n| lbl2               = Voice of Sapphire\n| data2              = [[Erica Luttrell]]\n| species            = Gem\n| gender             = Sexless<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/IAmA/comments/2e4gmx/i_am_rebecca_sugar_creator_of_steven_universe_and/cjw8ztw|website=[[Reddit.com]]|title=I am Rebecca Sugar, creator of Steven Universe, and former Adventure Time storyboarder, AMA!|last=Sugar|first=Rebecca|author-link=Rebecca Sugar|year=2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ianjq.tumblr.com/post/113794156834/i-know-that-the-gems-are-sexless-agendered-etc|website=[[Tumblr.com]]|title=IAN JQ dot com|last=Jones-Quartey|first=Ian|author-link=Ian Jones-Quartey|date=2015-03-16}}</ref> / [[Non-binary]] woman<ref>{{cite web |last1=Necessary |first1=Terra |title=Rebecca Sugar Opens Up About Being Non-binary |url=https://www.pride.com/comingout/2018/7/18/rebecca-sugar-opens-about-being-non-binary |website=[[Pride.com]] |date=July 18, 2018 |quote='''Sugar:''' [\u2026] the Gems are all non-binary women...They're coded female [\u2026] [T]hey appear to be female, but they're a little more representative of nonbinary women. They wouldn\u2019t think of themselves as women, but they're fine with being interpreted that way amongst humans.}}</ref> (female pronouns used)\n}}\n\n'''Garnet''' is a fictional character from the [[animated series]] ''[[Steven Universe]]'', created by [[Rebecca Sugar]]. She is a \"Gem\", a fictional alien being that exists as a magical [[gemstone]] projecting a holographic body. Garnet is a \"[[List of Steven Universe characters#Fusions|fusion]]\" \u2014 i.e., two Gems combining personalities and appearances as one shared holographic body \u2014 formed by two Gems named '''Ruby''' and '''Sapphire,''' who choose to remain permanently fused out of love for each other.\n\nGarnet is voiced by [[Estelle (musician)|Estelle]], a performance that has seen a positive reception. Garnet has been frequently praised for being a depiction of a positive [[lesbian]] relationship.\n\n==Character==\nThe de-facto leader of the Crystal Gems, who protect humanity and the Earth from danger,<ref name=AVJailBreak>{{cite web|url=http://www.avclub.com/tvclub/steven-universe-return-jail-break-216313|work=[[The A.V. Club]] |title=Steven Universe: \"The Return\"/\"Jail Break\"|last=Thurm|first=Eric|date=2015-03-12}}</ref> Garnet is initially presented as stoic and unfeeling but pragmatic and capable. The show's writers have described Garnet as characterized by great self-confidence; they represent this through the fact that she never asks questions.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.toonzone.net/sdcc2015-steven-universe-roundtable-interview/|publisher=Toonzone|title=SDCC2015: 'Steven Universe' Roundtable Interview|last=Glennon|first=Christopher|date=2015-07-22}}</ref> Eric Thurm of ''[[The A.V. Club]]'' described Garnet as \"initially the most reticent, distant, and simply alien\" of the Crystal Gems. After the Crystal Gems' original leader Rose Quartz gave her life to create her son [[Steven Universe (character)|Steven Universe]], Garnet took on the role of the group's ''de facto'' leader. Early in the series, she appears relatively distant, as she rarely speaks out.<ref name=AVTheAnswer>{{cite web|url=http://www.avclub.com/tvclub/garnet-gets-fairy-tale-steven-universe-origin-stor-230234|work=The A.V. Club |title=Garnet gets a fairy tale ''Steven Universe'' origin story|last=Thurm|first=Eric|date=2016-01-04}}</ref> As the story of ''Steven Universe'' progresses, however, she becomes more relatable. Writing for ''[[Minnesota Daily]]'', Cecilia Mazumdar Stanger pointed out that Garnet is far from a perfect leader and can make mistakes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mndaily.com/blogs/ae-blog/2014/09/07/steven-universe-boy-girl-power|work=[[Minnesota Daily]] |title=Steven Universe, the Boy with Girl Power|last=Stanger|first=Cecilia Mazumdar|date=2014-07-09}}</ref>\n\nFrom the gemstones in her palms, Garnet can summon two powered gauntlets. Her \"future vision\" allows her to view different possible outcomes to predict future events, and she can temporarily share this ability with Steven by kissing him. Eric Thurm noted that scenes in which Garnet uses her future vision are among the show's best visual accomplishments.<ref name=AVJailBreak /> Garnet also appears in the ''[[OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes]]'' [[crossover (fiction)|crossover]] episode \"Crossover Nexus\", in which she says that her visor helps her channel her future vision.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.animationmagazine.net/tv/cn-lines-up-ok-k-o-superhero-crossover-halloween-specials/|title=CN Lines Up \u2018OK K.O.!\u2019 Superhero Crossover, Halloween Specials|last=Mercedes|first=Milligan|date=September 24, 2018|website=Animation Magazine|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=January 25, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Ruby and Sapphire===\nAccording to Sugar, Garnet was intended to be a fusion since the [[pilot episode]], though Ruby and Sapphire came into focus while Sugar was writing for Garnet. Sugar described the process as \"[[reverse engineering]]\" the two personalities based on what the production team brought to the show.<ref name=Newsarama>{{cite web|url=http://www.newsarama.com/24809-steven-universe-creator-talks-jailbreak-future.html|work=[[Newsarama]] |title=New STEVEN UNIVERSE Episodes Beginning Of New Era For Show Says REBECCA SUGAR|last=Pitts|first=Lan|date=2015-06-12}}</ref>\n\nViewers learn that Garnet is a fusion in the first-season finale, \"[[Jail Break (Steven Universe)|Jail Break]]\", but foreshadowing in earlier episodes led many viewers to suspect it before it was revealed. Ruby is characterized as a feisty and aggressive fighter, while Sapphire is a stoic and contemplative [[oracle]], resulting in a complex dynamic between them. Garnet's stable relationship while fused is used as a metaphor for the power of healthy relationships, as Ruby and Sapphire together are stronger than any one Gem on their own.<ref name=AVJailBreak /> Garnet is described as being made of \"literal love, the romantic love of two queer individuals,\" as most Gems, including Ruby and Sapphire, present in a feminine manner.<ref name=MarySue>{{cite web|url=http://www.themarysue.com/steven-bomb-recap/|work=[[The Mary Sue]] |title=The Great Big Steven Universe Recap; Or, The Femme Smooch Heard 'Round the World|last=Kaiser|first=Vrai|date=2015-03-18}}</ref>\n\nThe second-season episode \"[[The Answer (Steven Universe)|The Answer]]\" features a flashback of Ruby and Sapphire's first meeting: Sapphire was a member of Blue Diamond's court who came to Earth to assist in the capture of Rose Quartz, and Ruby was one of her bodyguards. Ruby and Sapphire accidentally fuse for the first time when Ruby pushes her out of the way of danger, and they flee to escape execution for the taboo of mixed-Gem fusion. Garnet joins the Crystal Gems after encountering Rose Quartz, who tells her that Ruby and Sapphire's love is \"the answer\" to all her questions.<ref name=AVTheAnswer />  A later episode, \"Now We're Only Falling Apart\", reveals how Garnet's creation influenced Rose Quartz's ideals to fight for her right to exist.\n\nIn a story arc late in the fifth season, Garnet unfuses when Sapphire feels betrayed by Rose, who had encouraged their fusion in the first place, and parts ways with Ruby, saying that their relationship is based on a lie. As Sapphire learns Rose's full story from [[Pearl (Steven Universe)|Pearl]], Ruby realizes she has never spent any time exploring her identity apart from Sapphire, and leaves to embark on a quest of self-discovery. Eventually the two both realize that they still want to be together, and in the episode \"[[Reunited (Steven Universe)|Reunited]]\", they are [[Same-sex marriage|married]] as their way of being together on their own terms, rather than just because of Rose Quartz.\n\n==Reception==\n[[File:Estelle Swaray.jpg|thumb|Garnet is voiced by [[Estelle (musician)|Estelle]].]]\nGarnet is voiced by [[Estelle (musician)|Estelle]] in the original dub of ''Steven Universe''. Estelle's vocal performance is commonly praised by critics: Vrai Kaiser of ''[[The Mary Sue]]'' commended Estelle's voice work in \"Jail Break\" by stating that \"the amount of love, layers, and history she packs into so few words goes right to the heart no matter how many times you watch it.\"<ref name=MarySue /> Garnet's narration in \"The Answer\" was praised by Eric Thurn because Estelle got the opportunity to do voice work that was more fun and \"soft\".<ref name=AVTheAnswer /> AJ Adejare of ''The Fandom Post'' criticized the voice director of ''Steven Universe'' for under-utilizing Estelle's talents, as Garnet is mostly silent in the show.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fandompost.com/2015/03/26/steven-universe-season-one-review/|work=The Fandom Post |title=Steven Universe Season One Review|last=Adejare|first=AJ|date=2015-03-26}}</ref> Garnet is Estelle's first voice-over role, and the character was designed by Rebecca Sugar while she was listening to Estelle's music.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/video/comic-con-estelle-talks-abut-role-garnet-steven-26152823|work=[[ABC News]] |title=Estelle Talks About Her Role as Garnet on 'Steven Universe'}}</ref>\n\nGarnet has commonly been praised as a depiction of a romantic [[lesbian]] relationship in an animated series. Since 2010, animated television series such as ''[[The Loud House]]'' and ''[[The Legend of Korra]]'' have shown a larger amount of [[LGBT]] representation. ''Steven Universe'' makes frequent use of LGBT-related themes: [[Pearl (Steven Universe character)|Pearl]] has strong romantic feelings to Rose Quartz, and [[Stevonnie]] is a [[genderqueer]] character.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pinknews.co.uk/2015/07/17/comment-lots-of-childrens-programmes-already-have-lgbt-characters/|work=[[Pink News]] |title=Comment: Lots of children\u2019s programmes already have LGBT characters|last=Payton|first=Naith|date=2015-07-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metro.us/entertainment/four-cartoons-that-are-leading-the-way-in-lgbt-visibility/zsJogi---ekjB9tKntGMWg/|work=[[Metro New York]] |title=Four cartoons that are leading the way in LGBT visibility|last=Ewart|first=Asia|date=2015-06-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/cartoon-networks-steven-universe-includes-lesbian-couple_us_55ae61a0e4b07af29d565e34|work=[[The Huffington Post]] |title=Cartoon Network's 'Steven Universe' Includes Lesbian Couple|last=Nichols|first=James Michael|date=2015-07-21}}</ref>  Writing for ''[[The Lawrentian]]'' in January 2016, Bridget Keenan described Garnet as \"first canon lesbian couple on [[Cartoon Network]]\". However, Keenan also criticized Garnet for portraying as healthy a relationship that would realistically be \"unhealthy, unstable and controlling,\" as Ruby and Sapphire seemed completely controlled by the relationship.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lawrentian.com/archives/1007010|work=[[The Lawrentian]] |title=Why Steven Universe's \"Garnet\" is an unhealthy relationship|last=Keenan|first=Bridget|date=2016-01-22}}</ref>\n\n===Censorship===\nSome of the romantic interactions between Ruby and Sapphire have been [[censored]] during localization to other countries. In the [[Swedish language|Swedish]] translation of the episode \"Hit the Diamond\", flirting between the two characters was replaced with more neutral dialogue, causing controversy in Sweden; some fans of the series demanded that [[Cartoon Network (Nordic)|Cartoon Network Sweden]] not censor Ruby and Sapphire's relationship again.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/nojesbladet/tv/article22972478.ab |title=Lesbiska fl\u00f6rtscenen censurerades bort \u2013 i svenska versionen |trans-title=The lesbian flirt scene was censored \u2013 in the Swedish version |language=Swedish |author=Borgert, Linn\u00e9a |date=2016-06-10 |website=[[Aftonbladet]] |publisher=[[Schibsted]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160610080350/http://www.aftonbladet.se/nojesbladet/tv/article22972478.ab |archive-date=10 June 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160718224822/http://www.imdb.com/character/ch0524486/ Garnet] on [[IMDb]]\n\n{{Steven Universe}}\n\n[[Category:Steven Universe characters]]\n[[Category:Television characters introduced in 2013]]\n[[Category:Fictional extraterrestrial characters]]\n[[Category:Fictional characters with precognition]]\n[[Category:Fictional gemstones and jewelry]]\n[[Category:Fictional duos]]\n[[Category:Fictional LGBT couples]]\n[[Category:Fictional married couples]]\n[[Category:Fictional non-binary people]]\n[[Category:Fictional women soldiers and warriors]]\n[[Category:Female characters in animation]]\n[[Category:Female characters in television]]\n[[Category:LGBT characters in animation]]\n[[Category:Extraterrestrial superheroes]]\n[[Category:Fictional shapeshifters]]\n[[Category:Merged fictional characters]]\n[[Category:Fictional LGBT characters in television]]\n[[Category:Fictional LGBT characters in film]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-protected|reason=Persistent addition of [[WP:INTREF|unsourced or poorly sourced content]]|small=yes}}\n{{Redirect|Garnet (character)|other characters with the same name|Garnet (disambiguation)#Characters}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE: Garnet (''Steven Universe'')}}\n{{Infobox character\n| color              = maroon\n| name               = Garnet\n| series             = [[Steven Universe]]\n| image              = File:Garnet - Steven Universe.png\n| caption            = Garnet as she appears in \"[[Change Your Mind (Steven Universe)|Change Your Mind]]\"\n| first              = Garnet ([[Television pilot|Pilot]]; 2013)<br/>Ruby and Sapphire ([[Jail Break (Steven Universe)|Jail Break]]; 2015)\n| last               = Ruby and Sapphire (I am My Monster; 2020)<br>Garnet (The Future; 2020)\n| creator            = [[Rebecca Sugar]]\n| voice              = [[Estelle (musician)|Estelle]]\n| lbl1               = Voice of Ruby\n| data1              = [[Charlyne Yi]]\n| lbl2               = Voice of Sapphire\n| data2              = [[Erica Luttrell]]\n| species            = Gem\n| gender             = Sexless<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/IAmA/comments/2e4gmx/i_am_rebecca_sugar_creator_of_steven_universe_and/cjw8ztw|website=[[Reddit.com]]|title=I am Rebecca Sugar, creator of Steven Universe, and former Adventure Time storyboarder, AMA!|last=Sugar|first=Rebecca|author-link=Rebecca Sugar|year=2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ianjq.tumblr.com/post/113794156834/i-know-that-the-gems-are-sexless-agendered-etc|website=[[Tumblr.com]]|title=IAN JQ dot com|last=Jones-Quartey|first=Ian|author-link=Ian Jones-Quartey|date=2015-03-16}}</ref> / [[Non-binary]] woman<ref>{{cite web |last1=Necessary |first1=Terra |title=Rebecca Sugar Opens Up About Being Non-binary |url=https://www.pride.com/comingout/2018/7/18/rebecca-sugar-opens-about-being-non-binary |website=[[Pride.com]] |date=July 18, 2018 |quote='''Sugar:''' [\u2026] the Gems are all non-binary women...They're coded female [\u2026] [T]hey appear to be female, but they're a little more representative of nonbinary women. They wouldn\u2019t think of themselves as women, but they're fine with being interpreted that way amongst humans.}}</ref> (female pronouns used)\n}}\n\n'''Garnet''' is a fictional character from the [[animated series]] ''[[Steven Universe]]'', created by [[Rebecca Sugar]]. She is a \"Gem\", a fictional alien being that exists as a magical [[gemstone]] projecting a holographic body. Garnet is a \"[[List of Steven Universe characters#Fusions|fusion]]\" \u2014 i.e., two Gems combining personalities and appearances as one shared holographic body \u2014 formed by two Gems named '''Ruby''' and '''Sapphire,''' who choose to remain permanently fused out of love for each other.\n\nGarnet is voiced by [[Estelle (musician)|Estelle]], a performance that has seen a positive reception. Garnet has been frequently praised for being a depiction of a positive [[lesbian]] relationship.\n\n==Character==\nThe de-facto leader of the Crystal Gems, who protect humanity and the Earth from danger,<ref name=AVJailBreak>{{cite web|url=http://www.avclub.com/tvclub/steven-universe-return-jail-break-216313|work=[[The A.V. Club]] |title=Steven Universe: \"The Return\"/\"Jail Break\"|last=Thurm|first=Eric|date=2015-03-12}}</ref> Garnet is initially presented as stoic and unfeeling but pragmatic and capable. The show's writers have described Garnet as characterized by great self-confidence; they represent this through the fact that she never asks questions.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.toonzone.net/sdcc2015-steven-universe-roundtable-interview/|publisher=Toonzone|title=SDCC2015: 'Steven Universe' Roundtable Interview|last=Glennon|first=Christopher|date=2015-07-22}}</ref> Eric Thurm of ''[[The A.V. Club]]'' described Garnet as \"initially the most reticent, distant, and simply alien\" of the Crystal Gems. After the Crystal Gems' original leader Rose Quartz gave her life to create her son [[Steven Universe (character)|Steven Universe]], Garnet took on the role of the group's ''de facto'' leader. Early in the series, she appears relatively distant, as she rarely speaks out.<ref name=AVTheAnswer>{{cite web|url=http://www.avclub.com/tvclub/garnet-gets-fairy-tale-steven-universe-origin-stor-230234|work=The A.V. Club |title=Garnet gets a fairy tale ''Steven Universe'' origin story|last=Thurm|first=Eric|date=2016-01-04}}</ref> As the story of ''Steven Universe'' progresses, however, she becomes more relatable. Writing for ''[[Minnesota Daily]]'', Cecilia Mazumdar Stanger pointed out that Garnet is far from a perfect leader and can make mistakes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mndaily.com/blogs/ae-blog/2014/09/07/steven-universe-boy-girl-power|work=[[Minnesota Daily]] |title=Steven Universe, the Boy with Girl Power|last=Stanger|first=Cecilia Mazumdar|date=2014-07-09}}</ref>\n\nFrom the gemstones in her palms, Garnet can summon two powered gauntlets. Her \"future vision\" allows her to view different possible outcomes to predict future events, and she can temporarily share this ability with Steven by kissing him. Eric Thurm noted that scenes in which Garnet uses her future vision are among the show's best visual accomplishments.<ref name=AVJailBreak /> Garnet also appears in the ''[[OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes]]'' [[crossover (fiction)|crossover]] episode \"Crossover Nexus\", in which she says that her visor helps her channel her future vision.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.animationmagazine.net/tv/cn-lines-up-ok-k-o-superhero-crossover-halloween-specials/|title=CN Lines Up \u2018OK K.O.!\u2019 Superhero Crossover, Halloween Specials|last=Mercedes|first=Milligan|date=September 24, 2018|website=Animation Magazine|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=January 25, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Ruby and Sapphire===\nAccording to Sugar, Garnet was intended to be a fusion since the [[pilot episode]], though Ruby and Sapphire came into focus while Sugar was writing for Garnet. Sugar described the process as \"[[reverse engineering]]\" the two personalities based on what the production team brought to the show.<ref name=Newsarama>{{cite web|url=http://www.newsarama.com/24809-steven-universe-creator-talks-jailbreak-future.html|work=[[Newsarama]] |title=New STEVEN UNIVERSE Episodes Beginning Of New Era For Show Says REBECCA SUGAR|last=Pitts|first=Lan|date=2015-06-12}}</ref>\n\nViewers learn that Garnet is a fusion in the first-season finale, \"[[Jail Break (Steven Universe)|Jail Break]]\", but foreshadowing in earlier episodes led many viewers to suspect it before it was revealed. Ruby is characterized as a feisty and aggressive fighter, while Sapphire is a stoic and contemplative [[oracle]], resulting in a complex dynamic between them. Garnet's stable relationship while fused is used as a metaphor for the power of healthy relationships, as Ruby and Sapphire together are stronger than any one Gem on their own.<ref name=AVJailBreak /> Garnet is described as being made of \"literal love, the romantic love of two queer individuals,\" as most Gems, including Ruby and Sapphire, present in a feminine manner.<ref name=MarySue>{{cite web|url=http://www.themarysue.com/steven-bomb-recap/|work=[[The Mary Sue]] |title=The Great Big Steven Universe Recap; Or, The Femme Smooch Heard 'Round the World|last=Kaiser|first=Vrai|date=2015-03-18}}</ref>\n\nThe second-season episode \"[[The Answer (Steven Universe)|The Answer]]\" features a flashback of Ruby and Sapphire's first meeting: Sapphire was a member of Blue Diamond's court who came to Earth to assist in the capture of Rose Quartz, and Ruby was one of her bodyguards. Ruby and Sapphire accidentally fuse for the first time when Ruby pushes her out of the way of danger, and they flee to escape execution for the taboo of mixed-Gem fusion. Garnet joins the Crystal Gems after encountering Rose Quartz, who tells her that Ruby and Sapphire's love is \"the answer\" to all her questions.<ref name=AVTheAnswer />  A later episode, \"Now We're Only Falling Apart\", reveals how Garnet's creation influenced Rose Quartz's ideals to fight for her right to exist.\n\nIn a story arc late in the fifth season, Garnet unfuses when Sapphire feels betrayed by Rose, who had encouraged their fusion in the first place, and parts ways with Ruby, saying that their relationship is based on a lie. As Sapphire learns Rose's full story from [[Pearl (Steven Universe)|Pearl]], Ruby realizes she has never spent any time exploring her identity apart from Sapphire, and leaves to embark on a quest of self-discovery. Eventually the two both realize that they still want to be together, and in the episode \"[[Reunited (Steven Universe)|Reunited]]\", they are [[Same-sex marriage|married]] as their way of being together on their own terms, rather than just because of Rose Quartz.\n\n==Reception==\n[[File:Estelle Swaray.jpg|thumb|Garnet is voiced by [[Estelle (musician)|Estelle]].]]\nGarnet is voiced by [[Estelle (musician)|Estelle]] in the original dub of ''Steven Universe''. Estelle's vocal performance is commonly praised by critics: Vrai Kaiser of ''[[The Mary Sue]]'' commended Estelle's voice work in \"Jail Break\" by stating that \"the amount of love, layers, and history she packs into so few words goes right to the heart no matter how many times you watch it.\"<ref name=MarySue /> Garnet's narration in \"The Answer\" was praised by Eric Thurn because Estelle got the opportunity to do voice work that was more fun and \"soft\".<ref name=AVTheAnswer /> AJ Adejare of ''The Fandom Post'' criticized the voice director of ''Steven Universe'' for under-utilizing Estelle's talents, as Garnet is mostly silent in the show.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fandompost.com/2015/03/26/steven-universe-season-one-review/|work=The Fandom Post |title=Steven Universe Season One Review|last=Adejare|first=AJ|date=2015-03-26}}</ref> Garnet is Estelle's first voice-over role, and the character was designed by Rebecca Sugar while she was listening to Estelle's music.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/video/comic-con-estelle-talks-abut-role-garnet-steven-26152823|work=[[ABC News]] |title=Estelle Talks About Her Role as Garnet on 'Steven Universe'}}</ref>\n\nGarnet has commonly been praised as a depiction of a romantic [[lesbian]] relationship in an animated series. Since 2010, animated television series such as ''[[The Loud House]]'' and ''[[The Legend of Korra]]'' have shown a larger amount of [[LGBT]] representation. ''Steven Universe'' makes frequent use of LGBT-related themes: [[Pearl (Steven Universe character)|Pearl]] has strong romantic feelings to Rose Quartz, and [[Stevonnie]] is a [[genderqueer]] character.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pinknews.co.uk/2015/07/17/comment-lots-of-childrens-programmes-already-have-lgbt-characters/|work=[[Pink News]] |title=Comment: Lots of children\u2019s programmes already have LGBT characters|last=Payton|first=Naith|date=2015-07-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metro.us/entertainment/four-cartoons-that-are-leading-the-way-in-lgbt-visibility/zsJogi---ekjB9tKntGMWg/|work=[[Metro New York]] |title=Four cartoons that are leading the way in LGBT visibility|last=Ewart|first=Asia|date=2015-06-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/cartoon-networks-steven-universe-includes-lesbian-couple_us_55ae61a0e4b07af29d565e34|work=[[The Huffington Post]] |title=Cartoon Network's 'Steven Universe' Includes Lesbian Couple|last=Nichols|first=James Michael|date=2015-07-21}}</ref>  Writing for ''[[The Lawrentian]]'' in January 2016, Bridget Keenan described Garnet as \"first canon lesbian couple on [[Cartoon Network]]\". However, Keenan also criticized Garnet for portraying as healthy a relationship that would realistically be \"unhealthy, unstable and controlling,\" as Ruby and Sapphire seemed completely controlled by the relationship.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lawrentian.com/archives/1007010|work=[[The Lawrentian]] |title=Why Steven Universe's \"Garnet\" is an unhealthy relationship|last=Keenan|first=Bridget|date=2016-01-22}}</ref>\n\n===Censorship===\nSome of the romantic interactions between Ruby and Sapphire have been [[censored]] during localization to other countries. In the [[Swedish language|Swedish]] translation of the episode \"Hit the Diamond\", flirting between the two characters was replaced with more neutral dialogue, causing controversy in Sweden; some fans of the series demanded that [[Cartoon Network (Nordic)|Cartoon Network Sweden]] not censor Ruby and Sapphire's relationship again.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/nojesbladet/tv/article22972478.ab |title=Lesbiska fl\u00f6rtscenen censurerades bort \u2013 i svenska versionen |trans-title=The lesbian flirt scene was censored \u2013 in the Swedish version |language=Swedish |author=Borgert, Linn\u00e9a |date=2016-06-10 |website=[[Aftonbladet]] |publisher=[[Schibsted]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160610080350/http://www.aftonbladet.se/nojesbladet/tv/article22972478.ab |archive-date=10 June 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160718224822/http://www.imdb.com/character/ch0524486/ Garnet] on [[IMDb]]\n\n{{Steven Universe}}\n\n[[Category:Steven Universe characters]]\n[[Category:Television characters introduced in 2013]]\n[[Category:Fictional extraterrestrial characters]]\n[[Category:Fictional characters with precognition]]\n[[Category:Fictional gemstones and jewelry]]\n[[Category:Fictional duos]]\n[[Category:Fictional LGBT couples]]\n[[Category:Fictional married couples]]\n[[Category:Fictional non-binary people]]\n[[Category:Fictional women soldiers and warriors]]\n[[Category:Female characters in animation]]\n[[Category:Female characters in television]]\n[[Category:LGBT characters in animation]]\n[[Category:Extraterrestrial superheroes]]\n[[Category:Fictional shapeshifters]]\n[[Category:Merged fictional characters]]\n[[Category:Fictional LGBT characters in television]]\n[[Category:Fictional LGBT characters in film]]\n", "name_user": "Horseradishy", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Garnet_(Steven_Universe)"}
{"title_page": "Ratafia", "text_new": "[[File:Ratafia.JPG|thumb|right|140 px|Ratafia from [[Spain]]]]\n[[File:Ratafi\u00e0 di andorno.jpg|thumb|right|140 px|Ratafi\u00e0 di [[Andorno Micca|Andorno]]'' (Italy)]]\n'''Ratafia''' is a term used for two types of sweet alcoholic beverages and a flavouring essence whose taste resembles bitter almonds<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.nigella.com/ask/flavourings-for-christmas-baking | title = Flavourings for Christmas Baking | date = 11 December 2012 | first = Nigella | last = Lawson | work = Nigella.com | access-date = 21 May 2019}}</ref> and later to a ratafia flavoured biscuit or a biscuit to be eaten along with ratafia, and later still to a cherry variety.<ref name=\"ratafia-biscuit\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.british-history.ac.uk/no-series/traded-goods-dictionary/1550-1820/rape-vinegar-razed-ginger#h2-0007|title=Ratafia biscuit |website=British History Online|accessdate=2020-02-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.waitrose.com/home/recipes/food_glossary/ratafia_biscuits.html | title = Ratafia biscuits | work = Waitrose | publisher = [[Waitrose & Partners]] | date = | access-date = 21 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.bbc.com/food/ratafia_biscuits | title = Ratafia biscuits recipes | work = BBC Food | publisher = [[BBC|British Broadcasting Corporation]] | date =  | access-date = 21 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[Oxford English Dictionary]] earliest date of use: 1699.<ref name=\"ratafia-biscuit\"/>\n\n==Liqueur==\nThe first type of alcoholic beverage is a [[liqueur]] or [[cordial (medicine)|cordial]] \nflavoured with fruits or kernels, usually almond, or the kernels of peach, apricot or cherry.<ref name=\"ratafia-biscuit\"/> Ratafias were distinctive as the alcohol was not distilled, the flavouring ingredients being merely infused in it <ref>Froud and Turgeon (1961)</ref><ref name=\"ratafia-biscuit\"/> Ratafia may be flavored with [[lemon peel]] and spices in various amounts ([[nutmeg]], [[cinnamon]], [[clove]], [[Mentha|mint]], [[rosemary]], [[anise]], etc.), typically combined with sugar. Other flavorings can be used, such as vegetables and fresh herbs. The [[liqueur]] is typical of the Mediterranean areas of [[Spain]], [[Italy]], and north-east of [[France]] (Champagne and Burgundy). In the south-central region of Italy (specifically [[Molise]] and [[Abruzzo]]) Ratafi\u00e0 is made exclusively with fresh cherries and [[Montepulciano d'Abruzzo]] wines. \n\n==Fortified wine==\nThe second type, Ratafia fortified wine, is a type of ''[[mistelle]]'', a mixture of [[Pomace brandy|marc]] and the unfermented juice of the grape, and is the type produced in France. There are very few producers of Ratafia fortified wine. The fortified wine, one of which is made today in [[New Mexico wine|New Mexico]] by producer D.H. Lescombes, uses [[Moscato (grape)|Moscato]] grapes fortified with [[brandy]] to stop the fermentation early, which keeps the residual sugar high. The resulting wine is rich and sweet.\n\n==Biscuit==\n<blockquote>\"a small macaroon flavoured with almonds\"<br>\u2212 [[Collins English Dictionary]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.collinsdictionary.com/us/dictionary/english/ratafia-biscuit|title=Ratafia biscuit definition and meaning |website=Collins English Dictionary|accessdate=2020-02-03}}</ref></blockquote>\nRatafia Biscuits are made with ratafia essence, sweet almonds, apricot kernels, rosewater, egg white, sugar.<ref name=\"Regula-Ysewijn\">{{Cite web|url=https://app.ckbk.com/recipe/prid67377c06s001r010/18th-century-ratafia-biscuits|title=18th Century: Ratafia Biscuits from Pride and Pudding: The History of British Puddings, Savoury and Sweet by Regula Ysewijn|website=app.ckbk.com|accessdate=2020-02-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.food.com/recipe/ratafia-biscuits-109462|title=Ratafia Biscuits Recipe |website=Food.com |accessdate=2020-02-03}}</ref> Originally made with sweet and bitter almonds, now apricot kernels.<ref name=\"Regula-Ysewijn\"/> Amaretto is a ratafia liquor, thus the ratafia biscuits.<ref name=\"Regula-Ysewijn\"/>\n\nIn ''[[The Compleat Housewife]]'', [[Eliza Smith]] included a recipe for ''To make Ratafia Bisket'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://name.umdl.umich.edu/N04107.0001.001|title=The compleat housewife: or, Accomplish'd gentlewoman's companion: being a collection of several hundred of the most approved receipts, in cookery, pastry, confectionary, preserving, pickles, cakes, creams, jellies, made wines, cordials. And also bills of fare for every month in the year. : To which is added, a collection of near two hundred family receipts of medicines; viz. drinks, syrups, salves, ointments, and many other things of sovereign and approved efficacy in most distempers, pains, aches, wounds, sores, &c. never before made publick in these parts; fit either for private families, or such publick-spirited gentlewomen as would be beneficent to their poor neighbors. / By E. Smith.|first=E. (Eliza)|last=Smith|date=2004-12-03|accessdate=2020-02-03}}</ref> with the ingredients: bitter almonds, sugar and egg white, making it a confection that is very similar to a modern [[macaroon]].<ref name=\"ratafia-biscuit\"/><!-- Dictionary of Traded Goods and Commodities 1550-1820. Originally published by University of Wolverhampton, Wolverhampton, 2007. --><!-- British History Online is a not-for-profit digital library based at the Institute of Historical Research. --><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7OJQAQAAIAAJ|title=The Compleat Housewife: Or, Accomplish'd Gentlewoman's Companion:: Being a Collection of Upwards of Six Hundred of the Most Approved Receipts in Cookery, Pastry, Confectionary, Preserving, Pickles, Cakes, Creams, Jellies, Made Wines, Cordials. With Copper Plates Curiously Engraven for the Regular Disposition of Placing the Various Dishes and Courses. And Also Bills of Fare for Every Month in the Year. To which is Added, a Collection of Above Three Hundred Family Receipts of Medicines: Viz. Drinks, Syrups, Salves, Ointments ...|first=Eliza|last=Smith|date=1739-02-03|publisher=J. and J. Pemberton|accessdate=2020-02-03|via=Google Books}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://archive.org/details/2711361R.nlm.nih.gov|title=The compleat housewife, or, Accomplished gentlewoman's companion : being a collection of upwards of seven hundred of the most approved receipts in cookery, pastry, confectionary, potting, collaring, preserving, pickles, cakes, custards, creams, preserves, conserves, syrups, jellies, made wines, cordials, distilling, brewing : with copper plates, curiously engraven, for the regular disposition or placing of the various dishes and courses : and also, bills of fare for every month in the year : to which is added, a collection of three hundred receipts of medicines, consisting of drinks, syrups, salves, ointments, &c. which, after many years of experience, have been proved to be innocent in their application, and most salutary in their use : with directions for marketing|first=E. (Eliza)|last=Smith|date=1773-02-03|publisher=London : Printed for J. Buckland, J. and F. Rivington, J. Hinton, Hawes, Clarke and Collins, W. Johnston, C. Crowder, T. Longman, B. Law, T. Lowndes, S. Bladon, W. Nicoll, and C. and R. Ward|accessdate=2020-02-03|via=Internet Archive}}</ref>\n\n==Other Uses==\nRatafia essence was suggested in a BBC recipe in their 1940 publication, Food Facts For The Kitchen Front, for making mock marzipan, along with soya flour, margarine and sugar.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ekins |first1=Carolyn |title=Mock Marzipan No.100 |url=https://the1940sexperiment.com/2012/12/01/mock-marzipan-no-100/ |website=The 1940s Experiment |accessdate=29 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n'''Notes'''\n{{Reflist}}\n\n'''Sources'''\n*{{EB1911|wstitle=Ratafia|ref=none}}\n*{{NIE|title=Ratafia}}\n\n[[Category:Mistelle]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Ratafia.JPG|thumb|right|140 px|Ratafia from [[Spain]]]]\n[[File:Ratafi\u00e0 di andorno.jpg|thumb|right|140 px|Ratafi\u00e0 di [[Andorno Micca|Andorno]]'' (Italy)]]\n'''Ratafia''' is a term used for two types of sweet alcoholic beverages and a flavouring essence whose taste resembles bitter almonds<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.nigella.com/ask/flavourings-for-christmas-baking | title = Flavourings for Christmas Baking | date = 11 December 2012 | first = Nigella | last = Lawson | work = Nigella.com | access-date = 21 May 2019}}</ref> and later to a ratafia flavoured biscuit or a biscuit to be eaten along with ratafia, and later still to a cherry variety.<ref name=\"ratafia-biscuit\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.british-history.ac.uk/no-series/traded-goods-dictionary/1550-1820/rape-vinegar-razed-ginger#h2-0007|title=Ratafia biscuit |website=British History Online|accessdate=2020-02-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.waitrose.com/home/recipes/food_glossary/ratafia_biscuits.html | title = Ratafia biscuits | work = Waitrose | publisher = [[Waitrose & Partners]] | date = | access-date = 21 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.bbc.com/food/ratafia_biscuits | title = Ratafia biscuits recipes | work = BBC Food | publisher = [[BBC|British Broadcasting Corporation]] | date =  | access-date = 21 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[Oxford English Dictionary]] earliest date of use: 1699.<ref name=\"ratafia-biscuit\"/>\n\n==Liqueur==\nThe first type of alcoholic beverage is a [[liqueur]] or [[cordial (medicine)|cordial]] \nflavoured with fruits or kernels, usually almond, or the kernels of peach, apricot or cherry.<ref name=\"ratafia-biscuit\"/> Ratafias were distinctive as the alcohol was not distilled, the flavouring ingredients being merely infused in it <ref>Froud and Turgeon (1961)</ref><ref name=\"ratafia-biscuit\"/> Ratafia may be flavored with [[lemon peel]] and spices in various amounts ([[nutmeg]], [[cinnamon]], [[clove]], [[Mentha|mint]], [[rosemary]], [[anise]], etc.), typically combined with sugar. Other flavorings can be used, such as vegetables and fresh herbs. The [[liqueur]] is typical of the Mediterranean areas of [[Spain]], [[Italy]], and north-east of [[France]] (Champagne and Burgundy). In the south-central region of Italy (specifically [[Molise]] and [[Abruzzo]]) Ratafi\u00e0 is made exclusively with fresh cherries and [[Montepulciano d'Abruzzo]] wines. \n\n==Fortified wine==\nThe second type, Ratafia fortified wine, is a type of ''[[mistelle]]'', a mixture of [[Pomace brandy|marc]] and the unfermented juice of the grape, and is the type produced in France. There are very few producers of Ratafia fortified wine. The fortified wine, one of which is made today in [[New Mexico wine|New Mexico]] by producer D.H. Lescombes, uses [[Moscato (grape)|Moscato]] grapes fortified with [[brandy]] to stop the fermentation early, which keeps the residual sugar high. The resulting wine is rich and sweet.\n\n==Biscuit==\n<blockquote>\"a small macaroon flavoured with almonds\"<br>\u2212 [[Collins English Dictionary]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.collinsdictionary.com/us/dictionary/english/ratafia-biscuit|title=Ratafia biscuit definition and meaning |website=Collins English Dictionary|accessdate=2020-02-03}}</ref></blockquote>\nRatafia Biscuits are made with ratafia essence, sweet almonds, apricot kernels, rosewater, egg white, sugar.<ref name=\"Regula-Ysewijn\">{{Cite web|url=https://app.ckbk.com/recipe/prid67377c06s001r010/18th-century-ratafia-biscuits|title=18th Century: Ratafia Biscuits from Pride and Pudding: The History of British Puddings, Savoury and Sweet by Regula Ysewijn|website=app.ckbk.com|accessdate=2020-02-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.food.com/recipe/ratafia-biscuits-109462|title=Ratafia Biscuits Recipe |website=Food.com |accessdate=2020-02-03}}</ref> Originally made with sweet and bitter almonds, now apricot kernels.<ref name=\"Regula-Ysewijn\"/> Amaretto is a ratafia liquor, thus the ratafia biscuits.<ref name=\"Regula-Ysewijn\"/>\n\nIn ''[[The Compleat Housewife]]'', [[Eliza Smith]] included a recipe for ''To make Ratafia Bisket'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://name.umdl.umich.edu/N04107.0001.001|title=The compleat housewife: or, Accomplish'd gentlewoman's companion: being a collection of several hundred of the most approved receipts, in cookery, pastry, confectionary, preserving, pickles, cakes, creams, jellies, made wines, cordials. And also bills of fare for every month in the year. : To which is added, a collection of near two hundred family receipts of medicines; viz. drinks, syrups, salves, ointments, and many other things of sovereign and approved efficacy in most distempers, pains, aches, wounds, sores, &c. never before made publick in these parts; fit either for private families, or such publick-spirited gentlewomen as would be beneficent to their poor neighbors. / By E. Smith.|first=E. (Eliza)|last=Smith|date=2004-12-03|accessdate=2020-02-03}}</ref> with the ingredients: bitter almonds, sugar and egg white, making it a confection that is very similar to a modern [[macaroon]].<ref name=\"ratafia-biscuit\"/><!-- Dictionary of Traded Goods and Commodities 1550-1820. Originally published by University of Wolverhampton, Wolverhampton, 2007. --><!-- British History Online is a not-for-profit digital library based at the Institute of Historical Research. --><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7OJQAQAAIAAJ|title=The Compleat Housewife: Or, Accomplish'd Gentlewoman's Companion:: Being a Collection of Upwards of Six Hundred of the Most Approved Receipts in Cookery, Pastry, Confectionary, Preserving, Pickles, Cakes, Creams, Jellies, Made Wines, Cordials. With Copper Plates Curiously Engraven for the Regular Disposition of Placing the Various Dishes and Courses. And Also Bills of Fare for Every Month in the Year. To which is Added, a Collection of Above Three Hundred Family Receipts of Medicines: Viz. Drinks, Syrups, Salves, Ointments ...|first=Eliza|last=Smith|date=1739-02-03|publisher=J. and J. Pemberton|accessdate=2020-02-03|via=Google Books}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://archive.org/details/2711361R.nlm.nih.gov|title=The compleat housewife, or, Accomplished gentlewoman's companion : being a collection of upwards of seven hundred of the most approved receipts in cookery, pastry, confectionary, potting, collaring, preserving, pickles, cakes, custards, creams, preserves, conserves, syrups, jellies, made wines, cordials, distilling, brewing : with copper plates, curiously engraven, for the regular disposition or placing of the various dishes and courses : and also, bills of fare for every month in the year : to which is added, a collection of three hundred receipts of medicines, consisting of drinks, syrups, salves, ointments, &c. which, after many years of experience, have been proved to be innocent in their application, and most salutary in their use : with directions for marketing|first=E. (Eliza)|last=Smith|date=1773-02-03|publisher=London : Printed for J. Buckland, J. and F. Rivington, J. Hinton, Hawes, Clarke and Collins, W. Johnston, C. Crowder, T. Longman, B. Law, T. Lowndes, S. Bladon, W. Nicoll, and C. and R. Ward|accessdate=2020-02-03|via=Internet Archive}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n'''Notes'''\n{{Reflist}}\n\n'''Sources'''\n*{{EB1911|wstitle=Ratafia|ref=none}}\n*{{NIE|title=Ratafia}}\n\n[[Category:Mistelle]]\n", "name_user": "Cjmoss", "label": "safe", "comment": "Addition of historical use for ratafia essence", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ratafia"}
