itungwiza]], Bunjira played for [[Darryn Textiles F.C.|Darryn Textiles]], [[Motor Action F.C.|Blackpool]], [[CAPS United F.C.|CAPS United]], [[Free State Stars F. C.|QwaQwa Stars]], [[Bidvest Wits F.C.|Bidvest Wits]], [[Mamelodi Sundowns F.C.|Mamelodi Sundowns]], [[Jomo Cosmos F.C.|Jomo Cosmos]] and [[F.C. AK|FC AK]].<ref name = \"NFT\">{{cite web |url=http://www.national-football-teams.com/player/7417.html |title=Player profile |website=National-Football-Teams.com |accessdate=11 October 2015}}</ref>\n\nHe played for [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe]] between 1994 and 2001.<ref name = \"NFT\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Zimbabwe squad 2004 Africa Cup of Nations}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bunjira, Alois}}\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean footballers]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Motor Action F.C. players]]\n[[Category:CAPS United players]]\n[[Category:Free State Stars F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bidvest Wits F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Mamelodi Sundowns F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Jomo Cosmos F.C. players]]\n[[Category:F.C. AK players]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean expatriate sportspeople in South Africa]]\n[[Category:Expatriate soccer players in South Africa]]\n[[Category:2004 African Cup of Nations players]]\n\n\n{{Zimbabwe-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name           = Alois Bunjira\n|image          = \n|image_size     = \n|caption        = \n|fullname       = \n|birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1975|3|29|df=y}}\n|birth_place    = [[Chitungwiza]], Zimbabwe\n|height         = {{height|m=1.74}}<ref name = \"NFT\"/>\n|position       = [[Midfielder]]\n|youthyears1    = \n|youthclubs1    = \n|years1         = 1994\n|clubs1         = [[Darryn Textiles F.C.|Darryn Textiles]]\n|caps1          = \n|goals1         = \n|years2         = 1995\n|clubs2         = [[Motor Action F.C