king]]'' July ending theme\n|rowspan=\"2\"|''TBA''\n|-\n|{{nihongo|\"My Friend ~Arigato~\"|MY FRIEND \uff5e\u3042\u308a\u304c\u3068\u3046\uff5e|MY FRIEND ~Arigat\u014d~}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2012|12|12}}\n|B-side used for \"Vis\" advertisement campaign\n|}\n\n===Other appearances===\n*''Act4'' (8 December 2004)\n**Features the songs \"Himawari\", \"Deco Boco\", and \"Chocorate\" off of her single \"Himawari\"\n*''Tribute to [[Avril Lavigne]]: Master's Collection'' (25 October 2006)\n**Track 10: \"[[Sk8er Boi]]\"\n*''Yesterday Once More: Tribute to [[the Carpenters]]''\n**Track 6: \"[[Sing (The Carpenters song)|Sing]]\"\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.becky.ne.jp/index.php Official Sun Music website] {{in lang|ja}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20101009102338/http://emimusic.jp/artist/becky/ Official EMI Music Japan profile] {{in lang|ja}}\n*{{IMDb name|id=2114691|name=Becky}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Becky}}\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Kanagawa Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Japanese female pop singers]]\n[[Category:Japanese people of English descent]]\n[[Category:Japanese television personalities]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Kanagawa Prefecture]]\n[[Category:People who lost British citizenship]]\n[[Category:Asia University (Japan) alumni]]\n[[Category:20th-century Japanese women singers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Japanese singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Japanese women singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Japanese singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Japanese actresses]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Becky\n| image              = <!-- filename only, no \"File:\" or \"Image:\" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| alt                = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \u30d9\u30c3\u30ad\u30fc\n| native_name_lang   = ja\n| birth_name         = Rebecca Eri Rabone\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1984|03|06}}\n| birth_place        = [[Kanagawa Prefecture]], Japan\n| death_date         = <!-- {{Death date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (DEATH date then BIRTH date)  -->\n| death_place        = \n| nationality        = \n| other_names        = {{Nihongo|Becky\u266a\u266f|\u30d9\u30c3\u30ad\u30fc\u266a\u266f|Bekk\u012b}}\n| spouse             = {{marriage|[[Yasuyuki Kataoka]]|2019}}{{r|Marriage}}\n| children           = {{children|\n[[one]]| 2020}}\n| occupation         = {{flatlist| \n*Singer\n*Actress\n}}\n| years_active       = 1998&ndash;present\n| employer           = Sun Music Productions\n| website            = {{URL|www.becky.ne.jp}}\n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''Rebecca Eri Rabone'''|\u30ec\u30d9\u30c3\u30ab\u30fb\u82f1\u91cc\u30fb\u30ec\u30a4\u30dc\u30fc\u30f3|Rebekka Eri Reib\u014dn|born 6 March 1984}}, better known [[mononymously]] as {{Nihongo|'''Becky'''|\u30d9\u30c3\u30ad\u30fc|Bekk\u012b|}}, is a [[Japanese people|Japanese]] [[tarento]], currently signed to Sun Music Productions. Since 2009, she has recorded music under the stage name '''Becky\u266a\u266f.'''\n\n==History==\nBecky was born in [[Kanagawa Prefecture]] to a Japanese mother and an English father, Simon Rabone.<ref>http://aviation-business-gazette.com/A13/B72/Pilot-Simon-Charles-Rabone-Kawasaki-Kanagawa-.html{{Dead link|date=October 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.becky.ne.jp/contents/about.php|title=\u3079\u304d\u5b50\u88fd\u9244\u6240/\u6240\u9577|accessdate=12 March 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100402005626/http://www.becky.ne.jp/contents/about.php|archivedate=2 April 2010|url-status=dead}}</ref> She has one younger sister, dancer Jessica \"JJ\" Rabone.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ntv.co.jp/q/oa/20080511/01.html|title=\u4e16\u754c\u306e\u679c\u3066\u307e\u3067\u30a4\u30c3\u30c6Q!|date=11 May 2008|accessdate=12 March 2010| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100325183346/http://www.ntv.co.jp/q/oa/20080511/01.html| archivedate= 25 March 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/jjrabone/|title=JJ Rabone\u30b8\u30a7\u30b7\u30ab (@jjrabone) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=23 January 2019}}</ref> Until at least 2011, Becky held [[multiple citizenship|dual citizenship]] status in both Japan and the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kansai-collection.net/guest_becky.html |title=\u30b2\u30b9\u30c8 \u30d9\u30c3\u30ad\u30fc\u266a\uff03 {{!}} \u95a2\u897f\u30b3\u30ec\u30af\u30b7\u30e7\u30f3/KANSAI COLLECTION/2011 AUTUMN-WINTER/\u95a2\u30b3\u30ec\u30aa\u30d5\u30a3\u30b7\u30e3\u30ebweb |accessdate=14 November 2011 }}{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Although [[The Japan Times]] previously erroneously reported her full name as \"Rebecca Eri Ray Vaughan\",<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2016/01/23/national/media-national/smap-dodges-bullet-becky-isnt-lucky/ | title=SMAP dodges bullet; Becky isn\u2019t so lucky | publisher=japantimes.co.jp | date=23 January 2016 | accessdate=11 April 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160411100119/http://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2016/01/23/national/media-national/smap-dodges-bullet-becky-isnt-lucky/ | archive-date=11 April 2016 | url-status=live | df=dmy-all }}</ref> Australian airline [[Jetstar Airways]], having used her in advertisements and promotions aimed towards Japanese audiences,<ref>{{cite web | last = Easdown | first = Geoff | url = http://www.couriermail.com.au/business/jetstar-rocks-japan/story-e6freqmx-1111118451073?from=public_rss | title =  Against all odds, Jetstar rocks Japan | work = [[The Courier-Mail]] | date = 1 January 2009 | accessdate = 3 February 2009}}</ref> gives her full name as being \"Rebecca-Eri Rabone\",<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.etravelblackboardasia.com/article.asp?id=57012&nav=2 | title=Jetstar Enlists Japanese Icon \u2018Becky\u2019 to Boost Gold Coast Tourism | publisher=etravelblackboardasia.com | date= 12 November 2008 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20120229234704/http://www.etravelblackboardasia.com/article.asp?id=57012&nav=2|archivedate= 29 February 2012 | accessdate = 7 June 2015}}</ref> this surname matching that used by her father and sister; the error arises from the fact that 'Rabone' and 'Ray Vaughan' would be spelled the same way in Japanese.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://cleartalentgroup.com/client/jessica-rabone-educator/|title=Jessica Rabone -|last=Ciplex|website=cleartalentgroup.com|language=en|access-date=23 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190123224818/http://cleartalentgroup.com/client/jessica-rabone-educator/|archive-date=23 January 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bustle.com/articles/91933-who-is-jessica-rabone-on-so-you-think-you-can-dance-performing-got-her-out-of|title=Jessica Rabone Wows The Panel With Her Quirkiness|last=Young|first=Sage|website=Bustle|language=en|access-date=23 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190124041403/https://www.bustle.com/articles/91933-who-is-jessica-rabone-on-so-you-think-you-can-dance-performing-got-her-out-of|archive-date=24 January 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> \nShe debuted as a regular on the popular children's show ''[[Oha-Suta]]'' in 1999 reading out the English names of various [[Pok\u00e9mon]] characters in a section of the show called ''Pok\u00e9mon: The World''. She became a popular mascot of the show, and eventually started landing spots on various Japanese [[variety show]]s. On television, she has also appeared in numerous commercials and has lent her voice to the characters of many [[anime]] shorts and movies.\n\nShe graduated from Tokyo's [[Asia University (Japan)|Asia University]] with a degree in [[business administration]] on 15 March 2006.<ref>[http://www.nikkansports.com/ns/entertainment/p-et-tp0-060316-0009.html nikkansports.com] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090903014602/http://www.nikkansports.com/ns/entertainment/p-et-tp0-060316-0009.html |date=3 September 2009 }} 16 March 2006 \u7d4c\u55b6\u5b66\u90e8\u306b\u5165\u5b66,\u4e9c\u5927\u5352\u696d</ref>\n\nIn January 2016, Becky's reputation as Japan's most popular female personality took a negative hit after Japanese tabloid Shukan Bunshun revealed that she had an affair with musician [[Enon Kawatani]] who at the time was married. Following the scandal, Kawatani announced that he officially divorced his wife. In order to appease the public backlash and as a condition for her comeback to show business in Japan, Becky tried to officially apologize to Kawatani's wife. However, having no direct channel to her, Becky contacted the Shukan Bunshun\u2019s editorial department instead. Shukan Bunshun published the full contents of Becky\u2019s letter at the end of April 2016.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.japantoday.com/category/entertainment/view/end-of-a-saga-becky-to-return-to-showbiz-kawatani-divorces-wife-following-scandal |title=Archived copy |access-date=3 December 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161024090806/https://www.japantoday.com/category/entertainment/view/end-of-a-saga-becky-to-return-to-showbiz-kawatani-divorces-wife-following-scandal |archive-date=24 October 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> The letter acknowledges her affair but also implies that she has not seen Kawatani since the scandal broke and that she no longer has feelings for him. As a result of her apologies, Becky was to make her comeback with an appearance on TBS. In her first appearance back on TV, she appeared on \"Full Chorus - Music is Full Chorus\u201d on the cable channel BS Skyperfect TV.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.japantoday.com/category/entertainment/view/talent-becky-officially-returns-to-japanese-tv-after-affair-controversy |title=Archived copy |access-date=3 December 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161024090408/https://www.japantoday.com/category/entertainment/view/talent-becky-officially-returns-to-japanese-tv-after-affair-controversy |archive-date=24 October 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nOn 13 February 2019, Becky announced that she had gotten married to [[Yomiuri Giants]] coach [[Yasuyuki Kataoka]].<ref name=\"Marriage\">{{cite web |last1=Kishimoto |first1=Yu |title=TV personality Becky tweets she has married Yomiuri Giants coach Kataoka |url=https://mainichi.jp/english/articles/20190213/p2a/00m/0et/026000c |website=[[Mainichi Daily News]] |accessdate=17 February 2019 |location=Tokyo |language=en |date=13 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190214143048/https://mainichi.jp/english/articles/20190213/p2a/00m/0et/026000c |archive-date=14 February 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Variety shows===\nBecky is currently a regular panelist on the following programs:\n*''[[Pok\u00e9mon Sunday]]'' on [[TV Tokyo|TX]]\n*''[[Hanamaru Market]]'' on [[Tokyo Broadcasting System|TBS]]\n*''[[Gekko Ongaku-dan]]'' on [[Tokyo Broadcasting System|TBS]]\n*''[[Tensai! Shimura Zoo]]'' on [[Nippon Television|NTV]]\n*''[[Kiyoshi to Kono Yoru]]'' on [[Japan Broadcasting Corporation|NHK]]\n*''[[Watashi no Kimochi]]'' on [[Japan Broadcasting Corporation|NHK]]\n*''[[Nakai Masahiro no kin'y\u014dbi no Sma-tachi e]]'' on [[Tokyo Broadcasting System|TBS]]\n*''[[Tabegoro Manma!]]'' on [[Nippon Television|NTV]]\n*''[[Pittanko Kankan]]'' on [[Tokyo Broadcasting System|TBS]] as a semi-regular\n*''[[Sekai no Hate Made Itte-Q!]]'' on [[Nippon Television|NTV]] (2007-2016)\n*''[[Nazotoki Battle TORE!]]'' on [[Nippon Television|NTV]]\n\n===Television series===\n*''[[Churasan]]'' (NHK, 2001)\n*''[[Ultraman Cosmos]]'' (TBS, 2001)\n*''[[Ts\u016bhan Man]]'' (TV Asahi, 2002)\n*''[[Boku no Mahou Tsukai]]'' (NTV, 2003)\n*''[[Blue Moshiku wa Blue]]'' (NHK, 2003)\n*''[[Stand Up!!]]'' (TBS, 2003)\n*''[[Ace o Nerae!]]'' (TV Asahi, 2004)\n*''[[Hikeshiya Komachi]]'' (NHK, 2004)\n*''[[Rondo (tv series)|Rondo]]'' (TBS, 2006)\n*''[[Yaoh]]'' (TBS, 2006, in episode three)\n*''[[Toritsu Mizusho!]]'' (NTV, 2006)\n*''[[Taiyou no Uta (television personality)|Taiyou no Uta]]'' (TBS, 2006)\n*''[[Detective Conan]]'' (YTV, 2006)\n*''[[Anna-san no Omame]]'' (TV Asahi, 2006)\n*''[[Walkers (tv series)|Walkers]]'' (NHK, 2006)\n*''[[Nodame Cantabile|Nodame Cantabile Special Lesson (Europe Special)]]'' (Fuji TV, 2008)\n\n===Film===\n*''Noel'' (2003)\n*''Makoto'' (2005)\n*''Nodame Cantabile The Movie I'' (2009) - Tanya Vishnyova \n*''Nodame Cantabile The Movie II'' (2010) - Tanya Vishnyova \n*''[[Eight Ranger]]'' (2012) Momoko Kitoh \n*''[[Bokutachi no Koukan Nikki|The Last Chance: Diary of Comedians]]'' (2013) - Becky \n*''[[Eight Ranger 2]]'' (2014) - Momoko Kitoh\n*''JK Ninja Girls'' (2017)\n*''A Gambler's Odyssey 2020'' (2019)\n*''[[First Love (2019 film)|First Love]]'' (2019), Juri\n\n===Japanese dub===\n;Live-action\n*''[[Son of the Mask]]'' (2005), Tonya Avery ([[Traylor Howard]])\n*''[[Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles (2014 film)|Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles]]'' (2014), [[April O'Neil]] ([[Megan Fox]])<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.star-ch.jp/channel/detail.php?movie_id=23944|title= \u30df\u30e5\u30fc\u30bf\u30f3\u30c8\u30fb\u30bf\u30fc\u30c8\u30eb\u30ba\uff08\uff12\uff10\uff11\uff14\uff09|accessdate= January 13, 2020|work= Star Channel}}</ref>\n*''[[The Mummy (2017 film)|The Mummy]]'' (2017), Ahmanet ([[Sofia Boutella]])<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.star-ch.jp/channel/detail.php?movie_id=20816|title= \u30b6\u30fb\u30d5\u30a1\u30a4\u30bf\u30fc[\u5439]|accessdate= September 8, 2019|work= Star Channel}}</ref>\n;Animation\n*''[[Donkey Kong Country (TV series)|Donkey Kong Country]]'' (1999), Dixie Kong\n*''[[Oswald (TV series)|Oswald]]'' (2001), Daisy\n*''[[The Simpsons Movie]]'' (2007), Lisa\n*''[[Monsters vs. Aliens]]'' (2009), Susan Murphy/Ginormica\n\n==Discography==\nIn addition to her work as an actress and model, Becky has also had several musical releases. Beginning in late 2009, Becky began recording under the name {{nihongo|\"Becky\u266a\u266f\"|\u30d9\u30c3\u30ad\u30fc\u266a\u266f|Bekk\u012b}}, and her first single under [[EMI Music Japan]] debuted in the top 10 of the [[Oricon]]'s Daily and Weekly Charts.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/confidence/71398/full/|title=\u6b4c\u624b\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u306e\u30d9\u30c3\u30ad\u30fc\u266a\u266f\u304c\u521d\u306eTOP10\u5165\u308a|accessdate=28 December 2009|date=8 December 2009|work=[[Oricon]]|language=Japanese|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121020213539/http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/confidence/71398/full/|archive-date=20 October 2012|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Albums===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n! Title\n! Release date\n|-\n| {{nihongo|''[[Kokoro no Hoshi]]''|\u5fc3\u306e\u661f}}\n| {{start date|df=yes|2010|02|24}}\n|-\n| {{nihongo|''[[Kaze to Melody]]''|\u98a8\u3068\u30e1\u30ed\u30c7\u30a3\u30fc|Kaze to Merod\u012b}}\n| {{start date|df=yes|2011|07|13}}\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n! Stage name\n! Title\n! Release date\n! Notes\n! Album\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\"|Becky\n|{{nihongo|\"Sora Tobu Pok\u00e9mon Kids\"|<br>\u305d\u3089\u3068\u3076\u30dd\u30b1\u30e2\u30f3\u30ad\u30c3\u30ba|Sora Tobu Pok\u00e9mon Kizzu}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|1999|07|17}}\n|\n|rowspan=\"6\"|N/A\n|-\n|{{nihongo|\"Densetsu no Stafy\"|<br>\u4f1d\u8aac\u306e\u30b9\u30bf\u30d5\u30a3\u30fc|Densetsu no Sutaf\u012b}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2002|09|04}}\n|''[[Densetsu no Stafy (video game)|Densetsu no Stafy]]'' theme\n|-\n|{{nihongo|\"Sarara\"|<br>\u3055\u3089\u3089}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2002|12|04}}\n|\n|-\n|{{nihongo|\"Horiken Size II\"|<br>\u30db\u30ea\u30b1\u30f3\u30b5\u30a4\u30baII|Horiken Saizu II}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2003|03|12}}\n|\n|-\n|{{nihongo|\"Hello! Thank You!\"|<br>\u30cf\u30ed\u30fc\uff01\u30b5\u30f3\u30ad\u30e5\u30fc\uff01|Har\u014d! Sanky\u016b!}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2005|04|29}}\n|Pok\u00e9mon The Park theme\n|-\n|{{nihongo|\"Himawari\"|<br>\u5411\u65e5\u8475}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2006|02|22}}\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|Becky\u266a\u266f\n|{{nihongo|\"[[Kokoro Komete]]\"|<br>\u5fc3\u3053\u3081\u3066}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2009|12|02}}\n|B-side serves as ''[[Crayon Shin-chan]]'' theme\n|rowspan=\"2\"|''Kokoro no Hoshi''\n|-\n|{{nihongo|\"[[Suki Dakara]]\"|<br>\u597d\u304d\u3060\u304b\u3089}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2010|02|03}}\n|\n|-\n|{{nihongo|\"[[Emerald (Becky song)|Emerald]]\"|<br>\u30a8\u30e1\u30e9\u30eb\u30c9|Emerarudo}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2010|07|20}}\n|''[[How to Train Your Dragon (film)|How to Train Your Dragon]]'' Japanese theme\n|rowspan=\"4\"|''Kaze to Melody''\n|-\n|{{nihongo|\"[[Fuyusora no Love Song]]\"|<br>\u51ac\u7a7a\u306eLove Song}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2010|12|01}}\n|''[[Happy Music]]'' theme\n|-\n|{{nihongo|Goocky|\u30b0\u30c3\u30ad\u30fc|Gukk\u012b}}\n|\"[[Good Lucky!!!!!]]\"\n|{{start date|df=yes|2011|03|02}}\n|[[Universal Studios Japan]] 10th anniversary theme, Collaboration with [[Greeeen]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|Becky\u266a\u266f\n|{{nihongo|\"[[Kaze no Shirabe]]\"|<br>\u98a8\u306e\u3057\u3089\u3079}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2011|06|15}}\n|[[Universal Studios Japan]] 10th anniversary summer TV commercial song\n|-\n|{{nihongo|\"[[Yaruki Switch]]\"|<br>\u30e4\u30eb\u30ad\u30b9\u30a4\u30c3\u30c1|Yaruki Suitchi}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2012|06|27}}\n|''[[Onegai! Ranking]]'' July ending theme\n|rowspan=\"2\"|''TBA''\n|-\n|{{nihongo|\"My Friend ~Arigato~\"|MY FRIEND \uff5e\u3042\u308a\u304c\u3068\u3046\uff5e|MY FRIEND ~Arigat\u014d~}}\n|{{start date|df=yes|2012|12|12}}\n|B-side used for \"Vis\" advertisement campaign\n|}\n\n===Other appearances===\n*''Act4'' (8 December 2004)\n**Features the songs \"Himawari\", \"Deco Boco\", and \"Chocorate\" off of her single \"Himawari\"\n*''Tribute to [[Avril Lavigne]]: Master's Collection'' (25 October 2006)\n**Track 10: \"[[Sk8er Boi]]\"\n*''Yesterday Once More: Tribute to [[the Carpenters]]''\n**Track 6: \"[[Sing (The Carpenters song)|Sing]]\"\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.becky.ne.jp/index.php Official Sun Music website] {{in lang|ja}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20101009102338/http://emimusic.jp/artist/becky/ Official EMI Music Japan profile] {{in lang|ja}}\n*{{IMDb name|id=2114691|name=Becky}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Becky}}\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Kanagawa Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Japanese female pop singers]]\n[[Category:Japanese people of English descent]]\n[[Category:Japanese television personalities]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Kanagawa Prefecture]]\n[[Category:People who lost British citizenship]]\n[[Category:Asia University (Japan) alumni]]\n[[Category:20th-century Japanese women singers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Japanese singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Japanese women singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Japanese singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Japanese actresses]]\n", "name_user": "Jellysandwich0", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Becky_(television_personality)"}
{"title_page": "Kundai Benyu", "text_new": "{{short description|English-born Zimbabwean footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name           = Kundai Benyu\n|image          =\n|alt            = \n|caption        =  \n|fullname       = Kundai Leroy Jeremiah Benyu<ref name=\"Retained List 2016-17\">{{cite web|title=Retained List 2016-17|url=https://www.efl.com/siteassets/efl-documents/efl-released-and-retained-list---2016-17.pdf|publisher=English Football League|format=PDF|accessdate=21 July 2017}}</ref>\n|birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1997|12|12|df=y}}<ref name=\"11v11\">{{cite web\n| title = Kundai Benyu\n| url = https://www.11v11.com/players/kundai-benyu-248905/\n| publisher = 11v11\n| accessdate =21 July 2017}}</ref>\n|birth_place    = [[Camden Town]], England\n|height         = {{height|m=1.78}}<ref name=\"11v11\"/>\n|position       = [[Midfielder]]\n|currentclub    = [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]\n|clubnumber     = 26\n|youthyears1    = 2007\u20132016\n|youthclubs1    = [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]]\n|years1         = 2016\u20132017\n|clubs1         = [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]]\n|caps1          = 0\n|goals1         = 0\n|years2         = 2016\u20132017\n|clubs2         = \u2192 [[Aldershot Town F.C.|Aldershot Town]] (loan)\n|caps2          = 23\n|goals2         = 5\n|years3         = 2017\u2013\n|clubs3         = [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]\n|caps3          = 1\n|goals3         = 0\n|years4         = 2018\n|clubs4         = \u2192 [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]] (loan)\n|caps4          = 4\n|goals4         = 0\n|years5         = 2019\n|clubs5         = \u2192 [[Helsingborgs IF]] (loan)\n|caps5          = 10\n|goals5         = 1\n|nationalyears1 = 2017\u2013\n|nationalteam1  = [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe]]\n|nationalcaps1  = 2\n|nationalgoals1 = 0 \n|medaltemplates = \n|club-update    = 00:01, 3 June 2019 (UTC)\n|nationalteam-update = 11 November 2017 \n}}\n\n'''Kundai Leroy Jeremiah Benyu''' (born 12 December 1997) is an English-born Zimbabwean professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]].\n\n==Early life==\nBenyu was born to Zimbabwean parents on 12 December 1997 in [[Camden Town]], [[London]]. He grew up in [[Harlow]], [[Essex]].<ref name=\"BenyuCelt\">{{cite web | url=http://www.celticfc.net/news/12858 | title=Kundai: I was watching Cup final when I heard of Celtic's interest | publisher=Celtic FC | date=1 July 2017 | accessdate=1 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\n===Ipswich Town===\nBenyu joined [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]] at the age of nine,<ref name=\"BenyuCelt\"/> signing his first professional contract after turning 17.<ref>{{cite tweet |user=kundaibenyu_ |number= 568874388587749376 |date=20 February 2015 |title=Today I signed my first professional contract with Ipswich Town, thank you everyone who congratulated me #itfc }}</ref>\n\n===Aldershot Town (loan)===\nOn 7 December 2016, Benyu joined [[Aldershot Town F.C.|Aldershot Town]] on a one-month loan deal.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.theshots.co.uk/kundai-benyu/ | title=Shots agree to sign Tractor Boy Kundai | publisher=[[Aldershot Town F.C.|Aldershot Town]] | date=7 December 2016 | accessdate=29 June 2017}}</ref> The loan was subsequently extended several times, allowing Benyu to finish the 2016\u201317 season with the [[National League (division)|National League]] side.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.theshots.co.uk/kundai-extends-loan/ | title=Kundai extends loan | publisher=Aldershot Town FC | date=9 January 2017 | accessdate=29 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.theshots.co.uk/kundai-loan-extended/ | title=Kundai extends loan | publisher=Aldershot Town FC | date=3 February 2017 | accessdate=29 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.theshots.co.uk/kundai-extends-loan-2/ | title=Kundai extends loan | publisher=Aldershot Town FC | date=5 March 2017 | accessdate=29 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.theshots.co.uk/benyu-loan-season/ | title=Benyu loan extended for rest of season | publisher=Aldershot Town FC | date=30 March 2017 | accessdate=29 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Celtic===\nOn 29 June 2017, it was announced that Benyu had signed a four-year contract with [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.celticfc.net/news/12849 | title=Celtic delighted to sign Kundai Benyu on four-year deal | publisher=Celtic FC | date=29 June 2017 | accessdate=29 June 2017}}</ref> The midfielder scored on his first appearance for the club's [[Celtic F.C. Under-20s and Academy#Squad|development squad]], in a pre-season friendly against [[East Kilbride F.C.|East Kilbride]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.celticfc.net/news/12890 | title=New Bhoy on target as young Celts enjoy pre-season triumph | publisher=Celtic FC | date=8 July 2017 | accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref> Benyu made his competitive debut in Celtic's [[2017\u201318 UEFA Champions League qualifying phase and play-off round#Celtic v Linfield|4\u20130]] victory over [[Linfield F.C.|Linfield]] at [[Celtic Park]].<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40641442 | title=Celtic 4\u20130 Linfield | publisher=BBC Sport  | date=19 July 2017 | accessdate=20 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Oldham Athletic (loan)===\nOn 6 January 2018, Benyu joined [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]] on loan until the end of the 2017\u201318 season.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.celticfc.net/news/13791 | title=Benyu moves to Oldham on loan | publisher=Celtic FC | date=6 January 2018 | accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref> He made his league debut for the club on 13 January 2018 in a 1-1 home draw with [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]]. He was subbed off in the 74th minute, and replaced by [[Aaron Amadi-Holloway]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2018/01/13/england/league-one/oldham-athletic-afc/rotherham-united-fc/2468273/|title=Oldham Athletic vs. Rotherham United \u2013 13 January 2018 |work= Soccerway|publisher=Perform Group}}</ref>\n\n===Helsingborgs (loan)===\nBenyu joined Swedish club [[Helsingborgs IF]] on a season-long loan in February 2019.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11787/11648700/celtic-midfielder-kundai-benyu-joins-swedish-side-helsingborgs-on-loan |title=Celtic midfielder Kundai Benyu joins Swedish side Helsingborgs on loan |work= |publisher=Sky Sports |date=26 February 2019 |accessdate=26 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nBenyu's impressive performances for Aldershot Town earned him international recognition, receiving a call-up from [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe]] for their [[2019 Africa Cup of Nations qualification#Group G|2019 Africa Cup of Nations]] qualifier against [[Liberia national football team|Liberia]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.itfc.co.uk/news/2017/may/international-call-up-for-kundai/ | title=International call up for Kundai | publisher=Ipswich Town FC | date=19 May 2017 | accessdate=29 June 2017}}</ref>\n\nHe made his full international [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe]] debut in a 1\u20130 defeat to [[Lesotho national football team|Lesotho]] in [[Maseru]] on 8 November 2017.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.cosafa.com/lesotho-beat-zimbabwe-in-friendly/ | title=Lesotho beat Zimbabwe in friendly | publisher=COSAFA | date=9 November 2017 | accessdate=9 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played 20 January 2018|<ref name=\"soccerway\">{{soccerway|kundai-benyu/398279|accessdate=13 October 2017}}</ref>}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|National Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Ipswich T