ershot Town FC | date=9 January 2017 | accessdate=29 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.theshots.co.uk/kundai-loan-extended/ | title=Kundai extends loan | publisher=Aldershot Town FC | date=3 February 2017 | accessdate=29 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.theshots.co.uk/kundai-extends-loan-2/ | title=Kundai extends loan | publisher=Aldershot Town FC | date=5 March 2017 | accessdate=29 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.theshots.co.uk/benyu-loan-season/ | title=Benyu loan extended for rest of season | publisher=Aldershot Town FC | date=30 March 2017 | accessdate=29 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Celtic===\nOn 29 June 2017, it was announced that Benyu had signed a four-year contract with [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.celticfc.net/news/12849 | title=Celtic delighted to sign Kundai Benyu on four-year deal | publisher=Celtic FC | date=29 June 2017 | accessdate=29 June 2017}}</ref> The midfielder scored on his first appearance for the club's [[Celtic F.C. Under-20s and Academy#Squad|development squad]], in a pre-season friendly against [[East Kilbride F.C.|East Kilbride]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.celticfc.net/news/12890 | title=New Bhoy on target as young Celts enjoy pre-season triumph | publisher=Celtic FC | date=8 July 2017 | accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref> Benyu made his competitive debut in Celtic's [[2017\u201318 UEFA Champions League qualifying phase and play-off round#Celtic v Linfield|4\u20130]] victory over [[Linfield F.C.|Linfield]] at [[Celtic Park]].<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40641442 | title=Celtic 4\u20130 Linfield | publisher=BBC Sport  | date=19 July 2017 | accessdate=20 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Oldham Athletic (loan)===\nOn 6 January 2018, Benyu joined [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]] on loan until the end of the 2017\u201318 season.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.celticfc.net/news/13791 | title=Benyu moves to Oldham on loan | publisher=Celtic FC | date=6 January 2018 | accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref> He made his league debut for the club on 13 January 2018 in a 1-1 home draw with [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]]. He was subbed off in the 74th minute, and replaced by [[Aaron Amadi-Holloway]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2018/01/13/england/league-one/oldham-athletic-afc/rotherham-united-fc/2468273/|title=Oldham Athletic vs. Rotherham United \u2013 13 January 2018 |work= Soccerway|publisher=Perform Group}}</ref>\n\n===Helsingborgs (loan)===\nBenyu joined Swedish club [[Helsingborgs IF]] on a season-long loan in February 2019.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11787/11648700/celtic-midfielder-kundai-benyu-joins-swedish-side-helsingborgs-on-loan |title=Celtic midfielder Kundai Benyu joins Swedish side Helsingborgs on loan |work= |publisher=Sky Sports |date=26 February 2019 |accessdate=26 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nBenyu's impressive performances for Aldershot Town earned him international recognition, receiving a call-up from [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe]] for their [[2019 Africa Cup of Nations qualification#Group G|2019 Africa Cup of Nations]] qualifier against [[Liberia national football team|Liberia]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.itfc.co.uk/news/2017/may/international-call-up-for-kundai/ | title=International call up for Kundai | publisher=Ipswich Town FC | date=19 May 2017 | accessdate=29 June 2017}}</ref>\n\nHe made his full international [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe]] debut in a 1\u20130 defeat to [[Lesotho national football team|Lesotho]] in [[Maseru]] on 8 November 2017.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.cosafa.com/lesotho-beat-zimbabwe-in-friendly/ | title=Lesotho beat Zimbabwe in friendly | publisher=COSAFA | date=9 November 2017 | accessdate=9 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played 20 January 2018|<ref name=\"soccerway\">{{soccerway|kundai-benyu/